  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a single center, randomized, single blind study to compare the analgesic effect of
      different anesthesia and postoperative analgesic methods in uniportal VATS lung surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Combining epidural with general anesthesia is regarded as the gold standard of general
      thoracic surgery. The uniportal VATS lung surgery have advantages of minimal invasive
      surgical incision, less postoperative pain, and so on. Whether general anesthesia can become
      an alternative method of combining epidural with general anesthesia in uniportal VATS lung
      surgery, investigators thus plan to make a comparison on intraoperative stress response,
      postoperative pain, immune function of patients，and hospital expenses.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
